captions.text: We are here in Valdemorillo for the Red Bull Give Me Five.
It's a different type of racing, it's gonna be five riders, five laps, and a super fun track.
It's short, it's intense, it's just a lot quicker of a race and there are a lot of things you have to make happen right off the bat.
It's not a championship, it's only one race. For sure we're going to give our best.
All of the riders are pro, they ride GP so, it's for sure not gonna be easy.
I like a lot, the start with this double bump immediately, then the whoops waves. It's cool.
Also, there's nice jumps all over and it's fun.
Welcome to the quarter final of Red Bull Give Me Five!
It's quick, it's at fast pace, everybody is really sprinting. It's good though, it's good for the fans and good for the competition.
Give an applause for Jorge Prado!
Look at him go! He made it! Ryan Dungey goes head to head!
Ryan Dungey wins Red Bull Give Me Five!
Well this race, Red Bull Give Me Five, I've never done anything like it before, but it was fun.
I think the best form Europe was here and the best from the United States, and the fans... were unbelievable.

title: Offroad moto competition in Spain - Red Bull Give Me Five 2013
